		"Details": "The Dragon, DRG-1N, is a fast, beefy, heavy mech.   It doesn’t have the greatest hitting power, but it can stay in a fight.   Almost a company’s worth of worn-out DRG-1N chassis were sourced via various means to bring up to a more modern standard for the Taurian Concordat.  During the rebuilding process, the mech received the new Pafftek Industries MK1 Drone core, and the 300-fusion core was upgraded to a Light Fusion core to free up mass to allow for the upgraded systems.   The armament was mostly kept the same with only the Class-5 Autocannon being upgraded to an Ultra-5 Autocannon.  CASE protects both the left and the right torso of the mech from ammunition explosion by venting the damage out the back of the mech.   The LRM-10 gained a Fire control attachment for optimal performance on the DRG-1NTL variant.",
